T7 message_poller_no_trigger_row defect investigation
date=2026-05-25
workspace=/Users/gaganarora/Desktop/my projects/active_graph
scope=diagnostic_only
subject_run=T7 easy repetition run 014
subject_hash=T7_REPEAT_EASY_20260525_014

Summary verdict
===============

Run 014 is a real audit-chain failure. The original Theo -> Maya instruction
message exists in Supabase messages, Maya produced exact ACK messages and the
proof file, but no agent_triggers row exists for the original instruction
message_id. The runner therefore classified the task as
activation_path=message_poller_no_trigger_row, while the independent
canonical-trigger verifier correctly failed the run because no canonical Maya
trigger could anchor the ACK.

Most likely root cause: (b) Pentagon bug. The trigger creation path silently
skipped or failed for the original run-014 instruction even though the same
conversation and same native T7-easy instruction shape produced trigger rows
for runs 001-013, and later reverse/follow-up triggers were created normally in
the same conversation minutes later.

Recommended remediation category: Pentagon-side fix first. The correct
invariant is that every native instruction message intended for an agent must
create a durable agent_triggers row before any message-poller fallback can count
as activation. A bridge-side synthesized trigger would be a workaround, and
"known mode" should remain a verifier failure until the audit invariant is
restored.

T7 easy should not resume past this as green. Resume only if the operator either
accepts this as a known failing sample for variance accounting or fixes the
Pentagon trigger-creation invariant. The harness currently reports native_pass
for message_poller_no_trigger_row, which is too weak for verifier-bound T7.


