Runner code path:
  scripts/run-native-pentagon-task.mjs:
    insertMessage POSTs to /rest/v1/messages.
    triggerForMessage GETs /rest/v1/agent_triggers?message_id=eq.<message_id>.
    The runner waits up to 15 seconds for an initial trigger.
    The runner then polls until watch deadline.
    It only breaks early when finalTrigger has claimed_at and completed_at,
      responses.length is nonzero, and the proof file contains the hash.
    If the deadline arrives with finalTrigger still null but responses and proof
      exist, it records activation_path=message_poller_no_trigger_row and
      native_pass=true.

Interpretation:
  This is a deliberate runner fallback classification, not a bridge exception
  handler. It proves target-agent messages and proof existed, but it does not
  prove the audit-chain trigger row existed.


