Interpretation:
  The runner intentionally stopped the bridge before inserting the message, so
  bridge logs are not expected to show original-run processing. The native
  Pentagon app still observed and processed the message through a message-poller
  path. Because no agent_triggers row appeared within the runner's wait window
  or later DB audit, the harness classified a noncanonical activation path as a
  native pass. That is useful diagnostic signal, but insufficient for T7 audit
  success.


Bridge code and logs
====================

Bridge responsibilities observed in scripts/pentagon-trigger-bridge.mjs:
  pendingTriggers() queries existing unclaimed/incomplete agent_triggers.
  processCandidates() claims existing triggers, runs Codex, writes response
    messages, and marks trigger complete.
  checkPentagonWatchdog() detects stale existing native triggers and restarts
    Pentagon.app.
  The bridge does not insert agent_triggers rows for new messages.

